posts.plaintext:
Within MyComponent.module.scss we have css for both the heading of the component
and different font sizes for the title and the subtitle. So I want to be able to
add two classes to each element.

.heading {
  color: green;

  text-align: left;

  &**title {
    font-size: 3rem;
  }

  &**subtitle {
    font-size: 1rem;
  }
}


The easiest (and simplest IMO) way to do this is using template literals:

open the component.module.js file and import the scss module, and withing the
JSX add the classes as follows:

import styles from './MyComponent.module.scss'

<h1 className={`${styles.heading} ${styles.heading__title}`}> Title </h1>
<h2 className={`${styles.heading} ${styles.heading__subtitle}`}> Title </h2>
